Diagnosis. Distinguished by the male antennal segment I four times the width of other segments (
Fig. 14
); endosoma with medial left sclerite oval with microtrichia on surface ( Fig. 49 , 57 ) and ventral and dorsal right sclerites elliptical ( Fig. 55 , 58 ); posterior wall of female with rounded interramal lobes (
Fig. 104
), dorsal structure small, and medial process shaped as an inverted Y (
Fig. 104
